  "chapter": {
    "number": 32,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Joy of Forgiveness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "Of David. A Maskil.",
          {
            "noteId": 4342
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed is he whose transgressions are forgiven,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whose sins are covered.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4343
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed is the man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whose iniquity the LORD does not count against him,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4344
          },
          {
            "text": "in whose spirit there is no deceit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I kept silent, my bones became brittle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from my groaning all day long.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For day and night",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Your hand was heavy upon me;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "my strength was drained",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4345
          },
          {
            "text": "as in the summer heat.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I acknowledged my sin to You",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and did not hide my iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I said, “I will confess my transgressions to the LORD,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and You forgave the guilt of my sin.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore let all the godly pray to You",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while You may be found.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Surely when great waters rise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will not come near.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You are my hiding place.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You protect me from trouble;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You surround me with songs of deliverance.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will instruct you and teach you the way you should go;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will give you counsel and watch over you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be like the horse or mule,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "which have no understanding;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they must be controlled with bit and bridle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to make them come to you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Many are the sorrows of the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but loving devotion surrounds him who trusts in the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be glad in the LORD and rejoice, O righteous ones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "shout for joy, all you upright in heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4342,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Maskil is probably a musical or liturgical term; used for Psalms 32, 42, 44–45, 52–55, 74, 78, 88–89, and 142.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 32,
          "verse": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4343,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "LXX Blessed is he whose lawless acts are forgiven, whose sins are covered; cited in Romans 4:7",
        "reference": {
